Sentencas: The effect of cathode inlet gas humidification was studied on single anode supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFC's).
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The studied cells were Riso 2 G and 2.5 G.
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The former consists of a LSM:YSZ composite cathode, while the latter consists of a LSCF:CGO composite cathode on a CGO protection layer respectively.
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A clear effect of humidification was observed for 2 G cells with a fast transient upon humidification followed by an ongoing long term passivation/degradation during humidification.
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Removal of humidification resulted in a partial regain of the cell voltage prior to humidification.
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The humidification effect was found to be dependent on both the degree of humidification and the cathode polarization.
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: No significant effect of humidification was found at OCV which rules out the possibility of a traditional poisoning effect with a blocking of active sites.
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Post-mortem high resolution FEG-SEM analysis showed clear changes at and around the cathode/electrolyte contact area.
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In contrast to Riso 2 G cells, a very high tolerance towards humidification of cathode gas air was observed for Riso 2.5 G cells with no detectable effect of humidification even when the humidification was as high as 12.8 mol%.
Titulo: Effect of cathode gas humidification on performance and durability of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
